WEBVTT

00:02.920 --> 00:04.684
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:07.600 --> 00:09.602
[MAN PANTING]

00:21.840 --> 00:23.444
[MAN GRUNTS]

00:28.080 --> 00:30.651
No, no, no.

00:32.600 --> 00:34.602
[GRUNTS]

00:48.960 --> 00:50.644
[GRUNTS]

00:51.760 --> 00:54.889
Come on, man.
I'm just trying to make an honest living.

00:55.080 --> 00:57.048
There's nothing honest
about what you do.

00:57.560 --> 01:00.928
Who supplies you with Vertigo?
Tell me now and you live.

01:01.160 --> 01:03.128
Please! He'll kill me!

01:03.320 --> 01:05.607
Whoever you fear...

01:06.040 --> 01:07.610
...fear me more.

01:07.800 --> 01:09.529
Okay, okay!

01:10.400 --> 01:13.244
They call him The Count.
That's all I know.

01:13.600 --> 01:15.409
I swear to God!

01:18.840 --> 01:21.889
Hey! You get me down from here!

01:23.240 --> 01:26.483
DIGGLE: Find what you're looking for?
- Took down three Vertigo pushers.

01:26.680 --> 01:29.604
The last one finally knew a name.
The Count.

01:29.800 --> 01:32.201
The Count?
That's worse than The Hood.

01:32.560 --> 01:35.564
- You're not going back out there?
- I'm not done for the night.

01:35.840 --> 01:37.842
This Count has a lot of blood
on his hands.

01:38.040 --> 01:40.964
- It is long past time he started paying.
- Slow down.

01:41.200 --> 01:43.771
- I think you're missing the point here.
- What?

01:45.520 --> 01:48.171
- Thea.
- Her hearing's in a few hours.

01:48.480 --> 01:50.926
You think she cares more
about some drug lord...

01:51.120 --> 01:54.124
...or you being by her side
when she needs you the most?

02:00.040 --> 02:01.883
- Hey, we should get going.
- Heh.

02:02.080 --> 02:04.447
Judges don't appreciate the value
of being fashionably late.

02:04.680 --> 02:05.727
[CHUCKLES]

02:05.920 --> 02:09.163
- Got any other tips?
- Ahh, let the lawyer do all the talking.

02:09.360 --> 02:12.762
They give you a pad and paper,
but do not play tic-tac-toe.

02:12.960 --> 02:14.007
[CHUCKLES]

02:14.200 --> 02:16.567
Judges don't appreciate that either.

02:16.840 --> 02:18.171
[SIGHS]

02:18.920 --> 02:20.285
Come on, Speedy.

02:20.480 --> 02:22.562
I know. I know.

02:23.120 --> 02:25.566
I keep on trying to get up and go...

02:25.760 --> 02:29.287
...but, heh, I just don't.

02:30.240 --> 02:31.651
I wish Dad were here.

02:31.880 --> 02:32.927
[SIGHS]

02:33.120 --> 02:34.770
I'm here.

02:37.280 --> 02:39.567
We should leave now, Thea.

02:40.960 --> 02:42.928
MAN 1:
Miss Queen. Thea, over here.

02:43.120 --> 02:45.600
Can we get a comment?
Just one comment.

02:46.720 --> 02:48.563
Thea, are you going into rehab?

02:49.680 --> 02:51.921
MAN 2:
Are you being expelled from Balliol Prep?

02:52.120 --> 02:54.646
Are you worried about the outcome?

02:54.840 --> 02:58.083
"Docket ending 1-10-5-6,
People v. Thea Dearden Queen.

02:58.320 --> 03:01.722
Possession of a controlled substance.
Driving under the influence."

03:05.680 --> 03:08.809
Counselors, I understand
you've reached a plea agreement?

03:09.040 --> 03:11.327
We have.
Given that my client is a juvenile...

03:11.520 --> 03:13.522
...the people have agreed
to probation.

03:13.920 --> 03:15.684
A juvenile?

03:15.920 --> 03:17.604
Says right here she's 18.

03:17.840 --> 03:19.569
LAWYER:
She is 18 now, but at her arrest...

03:19.800 --> 03:22.531
...she was still two days shy
of her 18th birthday.

03:22.760 --> 03:25.764
- Miss Queen has no priors.
JUDGE: Just because Miss Queen's family...

03:25.960 --> 03:29.203
...sweeps her priors under the rug,
doesn't mean they don't exist.

03:29.400 --> 03:31.164
You get your client off.

03:31.360 --> 03:33.601
You help your boss
avoid dealing with a drug...

03:33.800 --> 03:36.087
...that's sweeping across our city
like a plague.

03:36.280 --> 03:38.044
Everyone wins, except us...

03:38.360 --> 03:40.886
...people of Starling City.
LAWYER: With all due respect...

03:41.080 --> 03:42.206
Miss Queen...

03:42.400 --> 03:45.847
...like it or not, you are now
the poster child for this menace.

03:46.040 --> 03:48.168
Maybe if people see
that the Queen family...

03:48.360 --> 03:50.442
...can't get away with using Vertigo...

03:50.760 --> 03:53.286
...they'll think twice
before using it themselves.

03:53.480 --> 03:55.926
The plea arrangement is denied.

03:56.800 --> 03:58.962
This case will proceed to trial.

03:59.160 --> 04:00.685
[SPECTATORS MURMURING]

04:00.920 --> 04:02.922
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

04:06.480 --> 04:07.925
MOIRA:
They can't do this.

04:08.120 --> 04:10.726
That man cannot send my daughter
to prison.

04:11.320 --> 04:12.526
What are our options?

04:12.720 --> 04:14.609
An interlocutory appeal.

04:14.800 --> 04:17.769
The trial judges have discretion
to reject plea agreements.

04:18.160 --> 04:20.208
You might prepare
for the possibility...

04:20.440 --> 04:22.886
...that this isn't gonna go our way.

04:23.720 --> 04:26.564
I'm sorry, Mrs. Queen.
I'll get to work on the appeal.

04:26.760 --> 04:27.807
[MOIRA SIGHS]

04:28.000 --> 04:33.086
Well, so much for the best
criminal defense attorney in the city.

04:34.480 --> 04:37.689
Thea, we will handle this. I promise.

04:37.920 --> 04:40.969
Like you promised Walter
you'd always stay faithful to him?

04:41.160 --> 04:43.970
- I feel better already.
- That's enough.

04:44.160 --> 04:48.210
Don't worry. Sounds like you won't have
to be putting up with me much longer.

04:51.200 --> 04:55.922
What, does she not realize
how serious this is? She took drugs.

04:57.080 --> 04:59.242
She drove.
She could have killed someone.

04:59.480 --> 05:00.686
- Or herself.
- I know.

05:00.880 --> 05:04.327
All that judge is looking for
is someone to make an example of.

05:05.280 --> 05:06.964
Why does it have to be her?

05:07.560 --> 05:09.449
Maybe it doesn't.

05:10.640 --> 05:14.167
Listen, I have to go do something.

05:14.600 --> 05:16.090
Are you gonna be okay?

05:17.920 --> 05:19.968
I'm not the one facing prison.

05:37.560 --> 05:38.846
Working for them now?

05:40.600 --> 05:42.489
Why are you doing this to me?

05:43.720 --> 05:45.006
I thought we were friends...

05:45.200 --> 05:48.249
...or something.

05:50.880 --> 05:55.169
Why'd you bother keeping me safe if
you were gonna hand me over to them?

06:01.880 --> 06:04.281
Just get me out of here, okay?

06:06.040 --> 06:07.929
I can't.

06:08.960 --> 06:11.122
Hey. Don't leave me here.

06:11.320 --> 06:13.288
I came back for you.

06:13.480 --> 06:15.084
Now you hear me.

06:15.280 --> 06:17.886
I came back for you!

06:31.400 --> 06:34.290
Looking for a Detective Hall.
I was told he works in Vice.

06:34.480 --> 06:36.289
Oliver?

06:37.200 --> 06:38.884
McKenna Hall.

06:39.320 --> 06:40.367
Hi, heh.

06:40.560 --> 06:43.882
Here I was, expecting a middle-aged guy
in a bad suit.

06:44.080 --> 06:45.809
And I got McKenna Hall.

06:46.000 --> 06:47.764
- I live to surprise.
- Oh.

06:48.120 --> 06:49.167
- I remember.
- Heh.

06:49.360 --> 06:51.806
What was that club you got us
kicked out of? The Club DeVille?

06:52.000 --> 06:55.163
In my defense there was no sign that
said you had to keep your clothes on.

06:55.360 --> 06:56.964
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

06:57.160 --> 07:00.369
So a cop. I guess you're not hitting
the party circuit anymore.

07:01.240 --> 07:04.210
I still go to raves.
I just go undercover now.

07:04.440 --> 07:06.761
And I have to dress
slightly more appropriately...

07:06.960 --> 07:09.406
- ...to hide my badge and gun.
- Right.

07:09.600 --> 07:11.523
So, what do you need with a vice cop?

07:12.240 --> 07:13.287
[SIGHS]

07:13.480 --> 07:16.927
- Vertigo.
- Right. I saw your sister on TV.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.925
- I'm sorry.
- The judge is making an example of her.

07:20.160 --> 07:24.529
So if you could find the person selling
drugs, it might take some heat off Thea.

07:24.800 --> 07:27.246
Easier said than done.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.842
Did some digging
and came up with a name.

07:30.040 --> 07:32.884
Um, The Count?

07:34.560 --> 07:36.449
We've known about The Count
for months.

07:36.680 --> 07:37.727
Oh.

07:37.920 --> 07:41.242
I wish this was thicker,
but we really don't have much on him.

07:41.880 --> 07:45.965
Love to say we're gonna catch him before
your sister's trial but it's unlikely.

07:46.440 --> 07:48.408
Oh, I'm late for my shift.

07:48.600 --> 07:53.606
Well, if you hear of anything
about this guy, just let me know?

07:55.600 --> 07:58.080
Always loved how much you
cared about your sister...

07:59.080 --> 08:01.606
...but leave the policing to the police.

08:01.920 --> 08:03.490
Okay.

08:14.000 --> 08:15.081
What did Queen want?

08:15.280 --> 08:18.284
He's an old friend.
His sister's jammed up.

08:19.000 --> 08:21.810
- Anything else, sergeant?
- No.

08:25.720 --> 08:26.767
[SIGHS]

08:31.280 --> 08:33.248
[DOOR OPENS]

08:35.760 --> 08:36.841
[GASPS]

08:40.799 --> 08:42.928
- You need a tailor.
- You know about the Hood.

08:43.159 --> 08:44.366
He just cornered me, man.

08:45.120 --> 08:46.451
The Hood guy?

08:46.640 --> 08:48.005
I didn't say anything.

08:48.280 --> 08:50.169
Oh, I know.

08:50.880 --> 08:52.609
You can't divulge secrets
you don't know.

08:52.840 --> 08:55.411
[CHUCKLES]

08:55.600 --> 08:58.968
But examples must be made.

09:02.640 --> 09:03.766
[GROANING]

09:03.960 --> 09:05.166
Vertigo...

09:05.360 --> 09:08.011
...in its purest form.

09:08.200 --> 09:10.043
When injected into the bloodstream...

09:10.240 --> 09:12.481
...affects the thalamus region
of your brain...

09:12.680 --> 09:16.969
...which is where all of the information
from your pain receptors is collected.

09:17.200 --> 09:19.931
No doubt you're in excruciating pain...

09:20.160 --> 09:21.810
...but actually you're not.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.207
You just think you are.

09:24.400 --> 09:26.084
I've seen it last for days...

09:26.280 --> 09:28.965
...until finally the heart gives out.

09:29.640 --> 09:31.642
[SCREAMING]

09:35.000 --> 09:37.082
One bullet left.

09:37.280 --> 09:38.850
[GROANING]

09:40.640 --> 09:45.362
Now, you can use that bullet to shoot me
and take your revenge...

09:45.600 --> 09:48.285
...or you could shoot yourself.

09:48.520 --> 09:50.204
[PANTING]

09:50.440 --> 09:51.521
It's your choice.

09:51.720 --> 09:53.404
[GRUNTING]

09:57.480 --> 09:59.847
[MAN SCREAMS]

10:05.680 --> 10:08.081
[GUNSHOT]

10:11.120 --> 10:13.088
The Hood...

10:13.600 --> 10:15.921
...coming for me.

10:18.000 --> 10:20.207
Interesting.

10:47.560 --> 10:49.642
I'm learning
you're not a morning snuggler.

10:49.840 --> 10:53.208
I'm learning you don't like to wake up
at any hour that ends in a.m.

10:53.400 --> 10:54.447
That's true. Yeah.

10:54.640 --> 10:59.043
So if you're busy being a lawyer all day
and I'm managing a nightclub all night...

10:59.240 --> 11:01.004
...when exactly do we get
to see each other?

11:01.200 --> 11:02.247
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

11:02.440 --> 11:05.091
Hmm, I got it. Stay.

11:10.200 --> 11:12.168
- Hey.
- Hey.

11:13.560 --> 11:15.369
Hey, how is Thea holding up?

11:15.560 --> 11:17.688
She's doing okay. Thank you.

11:17.880 --> 11:19.086
Um...

11:19.320 --> 11:23.086
Actually, uh, I came to talk to Laurel.

11:23.320 --> 11:24.731
Yeah.

11:25.000 --> 11:26.843
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:27.240 --> 11:29.288
Thank you for coming to court
yesterday.

11:29.480 --> 11:33.166
Of course. But I don't think the judge
is willing to move off his position.

11:33.960 --> 11:37.407
Taking a hard line against criminals
is a platform for his reelection.

11:37.600 --> 11:39.568
I need you to talk to your father.

11:39.800 --> 11:41.006
He's inside the system...

11:41.200 --> 11:44.363
...and maybe he cashes in a chip
with Judge Brackett...

11:44.560 --> 11:47.404
- ...gets him off throwing book at Thea.
- Oliver, I don't...

11:47.640 --> 11:52.248
Laurel, I am working on something
on my end...

11:53.840 --> 11:58.050
...but if it doesn't work out,
this is my best chance to help my sister.

11:59.440 --> 12:00.487
Please.

12:02.400 --> 12:04.448
I'll see what I can do.

12:04.640 --> 12:08.281
- But no promises.
- Thank you.

12:11.120 --> 12:12.485
Yep.

12:19.640 --> 12:20.801
[SIGHS]

12:21.000 --> 12:23.731
LANCE: Absolutely not.
- Dad, I know how you feel about Oliver.

12:23.920 --> 12:25.410
Then why would you even ask me?

12:25.600 --> 12:27.602
Because Thea,
she's only 18 years old.

12:27.800 --> 12:30.041
Which makes her an adult.
She can take medicine.

12:30.240 --> 12:32.561
It's about time somebody
in the Queen family did.

12:32.760 --> 12:34.250
What about the Lance family?

12:34.480 --> 12:37.962
A young girl acting out,
engaging in reckless behavior.

12:38.160 --> 12:40.049
Does that sound familiar?

12:40.240 --> 12:42.083
Laurel, don't go there.

12:42.320 --> 12:44.687
Thea, she's just like I remember Sara.

12:44.880 --> 12:46.962
That is not how I remember
your sister.

12:47.200 --> 12:49.851
Because you remember her
the way you wish she had been...

12:50.080 --> 12:52.048
...not the way that she actually was.

12:52.800 --> 12:54.848
She's not the saint
you make her out to be.

12:55.800 --> 12:59.646
I know she was arrested for shoplifting
and I know you made it go away.

12:59.960 --> 13:02.167
Well, maybe if I'd let her go to jail...

13:02.360 --> 13:04.408
...Queen wouldn't have had her
on that boat.

13:04.600 --> 13:07.729
Dad, you make it sound
like he kidnapped her.

13:08.640 --> 13:11.484
For so long, you and I have blamed
Oliver for Sara's death.

13:11.720 --> 13:14.200
But Sara's to blame too.

13:14.880 --> 13:18.726
When I look at Thea,
I see Sara's potential in her.

13:18.920 --> 13:20.843
And her flaws too.

13:21.040 --> 13:24.010
Yes, Thea made a mistake...

13:24.240 --> 13:26.641
...but she's been through a lot.

13:27.000 --> 13:30.004
She lost a father and a brother.

13:30.240 --> 13:32.481
She doesn't need prison.

13:32.760 --> 13:34.842
She needs help.

13:35.440 --> 13:36.680
So please...

13:43.880 --> 13:45.848
I'll make some calls.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.684
[DOOR OPENS]

13:54.880 --> 13:58.327
Seen a fair amount of Cyrillic
back in Afghanistan left over by Soviets.

13:58.920 --> 13:59.967
Is this Russian-owned?

14:00.160 --> 14:03.846
It's the not-so-hidden headquarters
of Starling City chapter of the Bratva.

14:04.120 --> 14:05.645
Diggle.

14:07.080 --> 14:08.969
Whatever I say.

14:09.320 --> 14:11.288
Whatever goes down.

14:11.880 --> 14:13.769
Just go with it.

14:15.240 --> 14:16.287
[IN RUSSIAN]

14:16.480 --> 14:18.084
Good to see you too.

14:18.720 --> 14:20.324
Long time.

14:20.520 --> 14:22.409
Particularly for Bratva captain.

14:22.600 --> 14:25.171
I was trying to figure out
where to put my interests.

14:25.360 --> 14:27.647
I decided on pharmaceuticals.

14:28.720 --> 14:30.927
I don't mean aspirin.

14:31.360 --> 14:32.691
A wise choice.

14:33.000 --> 14:36.641
Mephedrone would be
good investment for you.

14:36.840 --> 14:39.047
It's the newest thing.

14:39.240 --> 14:41.242
I was thinking Vertigo.

14:41.480 --> 14:42.686
Newer thing.

14:42.880 --> 14:45.247
Tough market, Vertigo.

14:45.480 --> 14:46.891
- Only one seller.
OLIVER: I know.

14:47.800 --> 14:50.280
Hoping you could do me a favor,
arrange a meeting.

14:51.680 --> 14:53.250
He is difficult man...

14:53.440 --> 14:55.886
...and he does not like new friends.

15:00.560 --> 15:02.767
This is everything the police
have on him.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.923
Tell him it's a gift.

15:09.280 --> 15:10.327
[SIGHS]

15:10.520 --> 15:12.488
I will see what I can do...

15:12.720 --> 15:15.530
...provided you do favor for me.

15:16.240 --> 15:17.321
[IN RUSSIAN]

15:20.680 --> 15:24.287
It is unusual for an American
to hold such a position...

15:24.520 --> 15:30.448
...of esteem in our organization,
Mr. Queen.

15:32.120 --> 15:33.485
Anatoli Knyazev...

15:33.680 --> 15:36.206
...he speaks very highly of you.
OLIVER: He should.

15:37.360 --> 15:38.441
I saved his life.

15:41.280 --> 15:42.611
[MAN GROANING]

15:42.800 --> 15:45.451
- What did he do?
- Something I told him not to.

15:46.400 --> 15:48.402
Now, the favor.

15:48.600 --> 15:50.125
Kill this man for me...

15:51.160 --> 15:55.324
...and I will believe your interest
in our organization is genuine.

15:55.760 --> 15:59.890
And then I will arrange
a meeting with The Count.

16:05.200 --> 16:07.601
DIGGLE: Oliver...
OLIVER: Hey, shut up.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.006
[GROANING]

16:26.480 --> 16:27.686
Spasiba.

16:27.920 --> 16:30.002
What are friends for?

16:32.440 --> 16:35.410
I'm out of the gate now.
What's going on?

16:35.720 --> 16:37.688
Are we getting out of here?

16:38.480 --> 16:40.209
Where are you taking me?

16:40.920 --> 16:43.321
[BOTH GRUNTING AND GROANING]

16:43.560 --> 16:45.562
[CROWD CHEERING]

17:14.440 --> 17:17.603
Well, I admit that bout
was particularly one-sided.

17:18.160 --> 17:20.208
Would anybody else like
to give it a try?

17:23.440 --> 17:26.648
The point of these little
gladiatorial distractions...

17:27.119 --> 17:30.090
...is to strengthen unit cohesion.

17:31.080 --> 17:33.765
To that end,
I think our newest recruit...

17:33.960 --> 17:38.204
...ought to be afforded
the opportunity to try his hand.

17:45.320 --> 17:46.560
MAN 1: Come on.
MAN 2: Hurry up.

17:46.720 --> 17:49.166
MAN 3: Get it on.
MAN 4: Get it over with.

17:51.600 --> 17:53.841
I can't believe you just killed that guy.

17:54.040 --> 17:56.930
You really have a low opinion of me.

17:58.160 --> 17:59.491
[TRUNK BEEPS]

18:07.400 --> 18:08.526
[GASPS]

18:08.720 --> 18:11.160
Whoa, that's a neat trick.
You going to teach me that one day?

18:11.360 --> 18:13.010
[GROANS]

18:14.320 --> 18:15.731
- No.
- What are you doing?

18:16.920 --> 18:19.800
You need to arrange a new identity
for this guy. Get him out of the city.

18:20.080 --> 18:23.641
So your Russki pal draws out The Count,
the vigilante takes him down.

18:23.840 --> 18:27.890
No, then the Bratva would know I used
them. That relationship is too valuable.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.168
I do the meet with The Count
as myself...

18:30.360 --> 18:33.364
...let him leave,
then we follow him to his hideout.

18:33.560 --> 18:36.643
- Just that easy, huh?
- I will still need my trusty bodyguard.

18:38.400 --> 18:43.167
Fantastic. Looking forward to my new
and exciting career as a drug dealer.

18:44.880 --> 18:47.121
He is a captain.

18:47.600 --> 18:50.080
And he has money.

18:50.840 --> 18:53.764
- Are you interested?
- Hmm.

18:54.280 --> 18:57.011
Let's say, yes.

19:01.520 --> 19:04.842
My father was able to get Brackett
to back off his hard line stance.

19:05.520 --> 19:07.249
Your father hates me.

19:07.440 --> 19:08.885
- No.
- No.

19:09.120 --> 19:11.009
My father hates him.

19:13.560 --> 19:15.961
- Nobody asked you to get involved.
- I did.

19:16.840 --> 19:18.808
LAUREL:
The judge has agreed to a sentence...

19:19.000 --> 19:21.002
...of 500 hours of community service...

19:21.200 --> 19:23.282
...and two years of probation.

19:23.880 --> 19:27.009
Provisional on the appointment
of someone to act in loco parentis.

19:27.200 --> 19:28.281
In loco what?

19:28.520 --> 19:30.921
It means the court
will appoint an individual...

19:31.120 --> 19:34.329
...to assume responsibility for you.

19:35.040 --> 19:36.565
Me.

19:36.760 --> 19:38.888
I say thanks, but no thanks.

19:39.080 --> 19:41.287
Thea,
you don't actually have a choice.

19:41.480 --> 19:43.926
Oh, actually, I do.

19:44.160 --> 19:47.209
See, I'm 18 now
and I can make my own decisions.

19:47.400 --> 19:53.043
So I decide not to be
your ex-girlfriend's office monkey.

19:54.600 --> 19:56.602
Well, if you change your mind, then.

20:04.320 --> 20:06.641
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

20:09.560 --> 20:11.210
Thea.

20:12.160 --> 20:14.561
You're in real trouble. And rightly so.

20:14.840 --> 20:17.525
Doing drugs and driving,
it is beyond stupid.

20:17.720 --> 20:21.167
That is a good deal that Laurel got you.
Why aren't you jumping at it?

20:21.400 --> 20:24.131
- I already have a mother.
- So...

20:24.360 --> 20:28.160
You're gonna go to jail,
and it will ruin the rest of your life.

20:28.520 --> 20:32.570
No, heh, I want to ruin Mom's life.

20:32.760 --> 20:36.401
She's a liar and a cheat.
I mean, deal with it, Ollie.

20:36.600 --> 20:41.003
You can pretend all you want to
that she's a saint, but I hate her.

20:41.200 --> 20:45.091
- And she betrayed Dad.
- So you're gonna go to jail to spite her?

20:46.160 --> 20:47.286
[CHUCKLES]

20:47.480 --> 20:48.766
Thea...

20:51.320 --> 20:53.800
...Mom didn't cheat on Dad.

20:54.600 --> 20:55.761
He cheated on her.

20:57.200 --> 20:59.248
Is that the best you can come up with?

21:00.960 --> 21:03.725
Dad wasn't the man he said he was.

21:04.800 --> 21:07.963
On the Queen's Gambit
right before he died...

21:08.280 --> 21:10.886
...he admitted to me that he failed us.

21:11.120 --> 21:15.648
You, me and Mom.

21:16.800 --> 21:19.326
That he wasn't the man
he said he was...

21:19.520 --> 21:22.046
...and that he just wished...

21:22.600 --> 21:23.806
[SIGHS]

21:24.600 --> 21:27.285
He wished he had more time
to right his wrongs.

21:28.960 --> 21:31.930
- I don't believe you.
- Yes, you do.

21:32.560 --> 21:35.404
- Speedy...
- Leave me alone.

21:41.080 --> 21:42.809
How dare you.

21:43.400 --> 21:45.641
She was old enough
to know the truth.

21:46.960 --> 21:49.486
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

21:54.920 --> 21:56.604
Oliver, the Russians called.

21:56.800 --> 21:59.531
The meet is set. It's tonight.

22:06.120 --> 22:09.169
ALEXI:
You know why they call him The Count?

22:09.760 --> 22:13.651
When he was developing this drug,
he experimented on the homeless.

22:14.160 --> 22:16.527
Prostitutes, runaways.

22:16.720 --> 22:20.486
The police would find their bodies,
puncture marks on their neck...

22:20.680 --> 22:22.045
...like a vampire.

22:26.200 --> 22:30.888
You should not be in such a hurry
to meet this man.

22:42.400 --> 22:43.526
Thank you for this.

22:44.480 --> 22:46.960
But I'm not overly concerned
about the S.C.P.D.

22:48.040 --> 22:52.329
Now, I understand you gentlemen wish
to participate in the feel-good business.

22:52.520 --> 22:55.410
- Yes.
- And why is that?

22:55.840 --> 22:58.923
I'm opening a nightclub.
I'd like my customers to have a little...

22:59.120 --> 23:00.485
[SIGHS]

23:00.960 --> 23:02.200
...something extra.

23:03.160 --> 23:07.609
Well, as it happens,
I'm looking to expand my brand.

23:12.280 --> 23:15.170
A good wine's value is measured
by its vintage.

23:15.360 --> 23:17.966
The number of years
it took to ferment.

23:18.520 --> 23:22.923
Vertigo is measured in lives.

23:26.320 --> 23:30.723
Fifty-six people died
to perfect this high.

23:30.920 --> 23:37.201
Believe me when I say
that they did not die for nothing.

23:46.680 --> 23:48.842
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

23:50.360 --> 23:54.649
MAN 1: Let's get out of here.
Come on, come on, let's go.

23:55.440 --> 23:57.727
- S.C.P.D. Put your weapons down!
MAN 2: Move, move.

23:58.880 --> 24:00.211
OFFICER:
S.C.P.D. Freeze.

24:02.360 --> 24:04.044
Get down!

24:08.280 --> 24:09.850
Oliver!

24:11.040 --> 24:12.929
[GRUNTS]

24:15.040 --> 24:17.088
[GROANING]

24:17.280 --> 24:18.566
No witnesses.

24:38.920 --> 24:39.967
Get out of the car.

24:40.200 --> 24:41.725
[GRUNTS]

24:41.920 --> 24:43.490
DIGGLE: You okay?
OLIVER: Keep it.

24:43.680 --> 24:46.411
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Got it, got it. Go. Steps, let's go.

24:49.720 --> 24:52.564
[GROANING]

24:54.560 --> 24:57.769
[DIGGLE PANTING]

25:06.080 --> 25:08.401
[GRUNTING]

25:08.760 --> 25:10.444
Oliver.

25:14.680 --> 25:16.250
Drink.

25:19.320 --> 25:21.288
[SCREAMING]

25:21.480 --> 25:23.369
[GROANING]

25:23.560 --> 25:24.971
[CROWD CHEERING]

25:32.560 --> 25:34.164
[BOTH GRUNTING AND GROANING]

25:39.640 --> 25:41.642
MAN 1: You're quick.
MAN 2: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

25:41.840 --> 25:44.127
MAN 3: All right.
MAN 4: Come on.

25:45.320 --> 25:46.367
[GROANING]

25:57.120 --> 25:58.645
[GASPS]

25:59.560 --> 26:01.050
Morning.

26:11.960 --> 26:13.291
How you feeling?

26:14.120 --> 26:18.409
I feel like I'm getting over
the worst hangover of my life. Argh.

26:18.600 --> 26:21.729
That coming from a guy who spent
most of his 20s in a hangover.

26:24.120 --> 26:25.451
Think you can uncuff me?

26:27.360 --> 26:28.964
I'm not gonna kill you.

26:30.320 --> 26:31.560
Promise.

26:36.800 --> 26:38.689
Ah.

26:43.760 --> 26:46.206
- Oh.
- You're standing. That's pretty impressive.

26:46.400 --> 26:48.243
[SIGHS]

26:50.160 --> 26:54.324
Count got you with half a dose but you
sweated out a small pool coming down.

26:54.880 --> 26:57.565
Ah, The Count.

26:58.200 --> 27:01.204
Any chance our friends
in S.C.P.D. took him down?

27:01.400 --> 27:04.051
None at all.
But we did manage to get this.

27:04.600 --> 27:06.728
I think we should analyze it.

27:07.600 --> 27:08.647
[SIGHS]

27:08.840 --> 27:10.683
Listen, maybe you need to give it
a few hours.

27:10.880 --> 27:14.089
A near drug overdose isn't something
you just walk away from.

27:16.880 --> 27:18.928
Neither is Thea.

27:26.600 --> 27:29.331
What's wrong?
ls everything okay with Thea?

27:29.520 --> 27:32.171
This isn't about your sister,
this is about you.

27:32.360 --> 27:34.522
Last night, we got a call from a Cl.

27:34.720 --> 27:37.803
Busted up a drug sale between
a bigtime dealer and Russian mob.

27:38.000 --> 27:40.890
"We"? I thought you worked Vice.

27:41.280 --> 27:42.327
Joint task force.

27:42.520 --> 27:45.683
- Vertigo's got everyone holding hands.
LANCE: Like I said...

27:46.080 --> 27:49.368
...last night, drug deal gone south.

27:51.080 --> 27:52.844
An eyewitness puts you at the scene.

27:53.240 --> 27:55.481
Whoever he is, he's mistaken.

27:55.680 --> 27:58.570
- Yeah?
- I saw you, Oliver.

28:01.560 --> 28:03.130
Is this true?

28:05.680 --> 28:07.409
I was checking into The Count.

28:07.600 --> 28:09.329
He's the guy who sold drugs to Thea.

28:09.520 --> 28:13.605
Figured I could find out what he looked
like, give your sketch artist something.

28:13.800 --> 28:17.964
I paid a lowlife with a Russian accent an
obscene amount to arrange a meeting.

28:18.160 --> 28:20.208
And did you get eyes on him?

28:20.400 --> 28:21.731
No.

28:21.920 --> 28:24.764
All right. Are you pressing charges
against my son?

28:24.960 --> 28:26.530
[SIGHS]

28:27.480 --> 28:29.960
Get involved again,
you'll see the inside of a cell.

28:30.160 --> 28:32.686
Unlike last time, you
will not see the way out.

28:32.880 --> 28:35.281
- Detective.
McKENNA: Thank you very much.

28:37.160 --> 28:39.891
Thank you for what you did for Thea.

28:40.280 --> 28:43.409
My daughter asked me for a favor
and I did it.

28:43.600 --> 28:45.602
And that's the end of it.

28:52.880 --> 28:55.201
- Hope you don't think I sold you out.
- No.

28:56.240 --> 28:57.321
Just doing your job.

29:01.760 --> 29:04.286
- What were you thinking?
- I was trying to help.

29:04.480 --> 29:07.882
By running around with the Russian mob
and a murderous drug dealer?

29:08.080 --> 29:11.562
- Are you out of your mind?
- Heh, Mom, look...

29:11.760 --> 29:15.810
...the real reason that you're upset is
because I told Thea the truth about Dad.

29:16.000 --> 29:19.083
- She never needed to know that.
THEA: Yes, I did.

29:20.760 --> 29:23.809
I'm old enough to know the truth,
Mom.

29:25.200 --> 29:26.281
Mom...

29:27.720 --> 29:29.927
It wasn't about your age.

29:32.040 --> 29:35.840
It was about preserving your memory
of your father.

29:37.640 --> 29:39.051
He loved you.

29:39.760 --> 29:42.684
No matter his faults, he loved you.

29:44.360 --> 29:46.727
I said that I wished...

29:46.920 --> 29:52.609
...you had died instead of him,
but you still didn't say anything.

29:52.800 --> 29:53.926
Why?

29:56.000 --> 29:57.968
One day...

29:59.080 --> 30:02.243
...I hope you're lucky enough
to have a daughter...

30:02.800 --> 30:04.882
...and you'll know why.

30:07.560 --> 30:09.642
I'm so sorry for what I said.

30:09.840 --> 30:12.366
I know, I know.

30:13.240 --> 30:15.242
[BOTH SOBBING]

30:24.120 --> 30:27.408
- Now what?
- Like you said, we analyze the Vertigo.

30:27.600 --> 30:29.329
It's liquid form, it contains water.

30:29.520 --> 30:33.320
So maybe we can trace back
to where in the city The Count is...

30:35.680 --> 30:37.364
...cooking up this garbage.

30:37.600 --> 30:38.965
[GRUNTS]

30:39.160 --> 30:40.207
[PANTS]

30:40.440 --> 30:42.807
DIGGLE:
Oliver? Oliver.

30:44.320 --> 30:46.448
[GRUNTS]

30:55.600 --> 30:58.285
[IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

31:34.400 --> 31:35.640
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

31:38.480 --> 31:41.609
- Hey, we need to get you to a hospital.
- No.

31:42.080 --> 31:45.607
Oliver, God knows what's in that drug.
It could be causing permanent damage.

31:45.840 --> 31:49.845
Ahem, Felicity.
Hey, they said you'd be up here.

31:50.120 --> 31:52.202
You look like something
the cat dragged in.

31:52.400 --> 31:54.448
Not that there are cats
in this building.

31:54.680 --> 31:57.923
Well, once a cat did get in,
but a guard Tased it.

31:58.120 --> 32:01.329
It smelled like fur and static in here
for, like, a week.

32:03.160 --> 32:05.561
Ahem, you mind stepping away
from the window?

32:05.760 --> 32:07.762
I have a little bit of a hangover.

32:07.960 --> 32:10.486
Sounds like you need a Bloody Mary
and a pretzel...

32:10.680 --> 32:12.045
...not the IT Department.

32:12.280 --> 32:15.284
Actually, my buddy Kevin
is starting an energy drink company.

32:15.480 --> 32:18.165
He says it's fantastic
for curing hangovers...

32:18.360 --> 32:22.285
...but I am very particular
about what it is I put in my body.

32:22.480 --> 32:24.244
I've noticed.

32:24.440 --> 32:26.727
I said, "not noticed," right?

32:26.960 --> 32:29.088
[CHUCKLES]

32:29.280 --> 32:30.520
Trying to find a secret recipe.

32:30.760 --> 32:33.001
Could you do a spectro-analysis
of the sample...

32:33.200 --> 32:36.010
...and find out exactly
where in the city it's made?

32:37.720 --> 32:41.441
If it's an energy drink,
why is it in a syringe?

32:42.560 --> 32:45.166
I ran out of sports bottles.

32:50.880 --> 32:52.245
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

32:53.280 --> 32:54.850
[ELEVATOR OPENS]

32:55.040 --> 32:57.805
Your BS stories are getting worse.

32:58.280 --> 33:00.248
Well aware.

33:01.080 --> 33:02.684
DIGGLE:
Looks like Felicity came through.

33:03.280 --> 33:06.045
The solvent used in the Vertigo sample
was runoff water...

33:06.240 --> 33:11.451
...originated within a 10-block radius
of where East Glades meets the bay.

33:11.640 --> 33:16.089
Nothing there except an old detention
center abandoned about three years ago.

33:16.280 --> 33:17.327
Cutbacks.

33:20.600 --> 33:24.366
You can't go out there, Oliver. Still
suffering the aftereffects of Vertigo.

33:24.600 --> 33:27.683
Did you hear The Count?
He's taking this drug citywide.

33:27.880 --> 33:29.928
We don't stop him,
this becomes an epidemic.

33:30.120 --> 33:31.724
I can stop you from leaving.

33:35.720 --> 33:36.926
Try.

33:43.800 --> 33:45.609
DIGGLE:
Oliver, hit this and you can leave.

34:01.520 --> 34:03.045
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

34:10.800 --> 34:13.087
I'm glad you came to your senses.

34:14.159 --> 34:15.924
You should remember one thing, Dig.

34:16.120 --> 34:19.329
- What's that?
- I don't need the bow.

34:24.159 --> 34:26.161
[SCOFFS]

34:34.320 --> 34:37.324
[MEN GRUNT]

34:54.000 --> 34:55.364
[GROANING]

35:06.360 --> 35:08.647
[MAN SCREAMS]

35:13.760 --> 35:17.162
- My Cl swears this is the place.
- Bring your men up on the flank.

35:17.360 --> 35:19.806
- Okay, this way.
- Follow me.

35:20.520 --> 35:22.363
- He's here!
- He who?

35:22.560 --> 35:23.766
The Hood!

35:38.000 --> 35:39.570
[GUNFIRE]

35:40.600 --> 35:42.728
Looks like we're not the only guests.

35:43.800 --> 35:45.962
You should have stuck
to your depraved elite.

35:46.280 --> 35:49.250
I'm merely providing people
with what they want.

35:49.440 --> 35:53.126
- I'm providing a public service.
- So am I.

36:03.560 --> 36:05.483
[GROANS]

36:05.720 --> 36:08.087
Enjoy the fruits of your labor.

36:11.000 --> 36:12.729
Freeze!

36:12.920 --> 36:16.288
Put down the needle
or I will shoot you.

36:22.600 --> 36:24.250
[GRUNTS]

36:24.440 --> 36:26.408
- Put down the syringe.
OLIVER: He deserves this.

36:26.600 --> 36:29.251
Not according to the law.
People think you're a hero...

36:29.440 --> 36:31.920
...people like my daughter
if they could see you now.

36:32.160 --> 36:33.241
You're no hero.

36:34.560 --> 36:37.245
You're what I always said you were.

36:38.080 --> 36:39.889
A killer.

36:42.280 --> 36:43.884
Get him.

36:49.960 --> 36:51.928
Get me an ambulance. Now.

36:57.720 --> 36:59.768
Juvenile delinquent
reporting for duty.

36:59.960 --> 37:02.406
Heh, since you lost your license,
I'll pick you up at 5.

37:02.600 --> 37:05.080
Six.
We have a lot of work for her to do.

37:05.320 --> 37:07.766
Well, then, let's say 7, just to be safe.

37:07.960 --> 37:09.450
Is it too late to choose jail?

37:09.640 --> 37:11.847
OLIVER & LAUREL:
Yes, ha-ha-ha.

37:12.080 --> 37:15.084
I need you to go through these files,
and pull out the documents...

37:15.280 --> 37:16.486
...dated March 2007.

37:16.680 --> 37:18.330
Do you think you could do that?

37:18.520 --> 37:20.488
I think I can, heh.

37:22.200 --> 37:24.407
Look, I know I messed up.

37:25.880 --> 37:28.121
I really appreciate this, Laurel.

37:28.320 --> 37:31.961
We're gonna make an upstanding citizen
out of you yet, Speedy.

37:32.160 --> 37:33.525
[CHUCKLES]

37:34.360 --> 37:37.284
Thank you. This will be good for her
having a role model...

37:37.520 --> 37:40.490
- ...somebody better than me.
- Oh, you're not so bad.

37:40.680 --> 37:42.967
And besides, it will be nice
to have her around.

37:43.160 --> 37:45.003
[PHONE RINGING]

37:46.920 --> 37:48.570
I gotta take this. Excuse me.

37:49.680 --> 37:51.728
- Hello.
McKENNA [OVER PHONE]: I got the Count.

37:51.920 --> 37:56.005
Bust up his lab, got him on everything
from drug trafficking to homicide.

37:56.200 --> 37:59.807
- He'll be gone for a long while.
- That's great. Thanks.

38:00.040 --> 38:02.520
It was great seeing you, Oliver, heh.

38:02.800 --> 38:04.529
You too.

38:05.280 --> 38:07.009
[OVER PHONE] See you.

38:11.520 --> 38:13.329
He's still critical.

38:13.560 --> 38:16.325
I've never seen anyone OD
on this much Vertigo and live.

38:16.560 --> 38:19.404
There's just no way of knowing
what damage has been done...

38:19.600 --> 38:22.683
...to his brain and nervous system,
or if it's irreparable.

38:22.880 --> 38:24.882
[GROANING]

38:26.120 --> 38:29.249
[COUNT SCREAMING]

38:49.520 --> 38:51.568
[GASPING]

38:56.400 --> 38:57.481
[COUGHING]

38:59.920 --> 39:01.922
[PANTING]

39:03.680 --> 39:05.682
[PANTING]

39:34.160 --> 39:36.208
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

39:38.400 --> 39:40.243
"Survive."

39:59.760 --> 40:01.000
- Hi.
- Hi.

40:01.200 --> 40:05.046
Thanks for meeting me.
I was nervous to come to your house, heh.

40:05.480 --> 40:06.641
Okay, heh.

40:07.960 --> 40:12.727
The thing is, I've been debating whether
or not to share this with you for weeks.

40:14.400 --> 40:16.402
Can I trust you?

40:17.240 --> 40:21.370
I'm not an idiot. You've dropped
some fairly ridiculous lies on me...

40:21.600 --> 40:26.208
...and yet I still feel
like I can trust you, heh.

40:26.440 --> 40:27.930
[CHUCKLES]

40:28.960 --> 40:30.121
Why is that?

40:30.360 --> 40:31.646
I have one of those faces.

40:31.840 --> 40:33.683
[OLIVER CHUCKLES]

40:34.560 --> 40:36.210
Sorry.

40:36.800 --> 40:38.290
Yes.

40:39.600 --> 40:41.284
You can trust me.

40:43.520 --> 40:45.204
Then I have something to show you.

41:07.760 --> 41:09.649
Have you ever seen this before?

41:09.840 --> 41:11.444
No.

41:13.640 --> 41:15.563
Where'd you get it?

41:16.320 --> 41:18.322
From your stepfather.

41:22.520 --> 41:23.806
It's from Walter.

41:24.040 --> 41:25.724
Uh...

41:26.800 --> 41:28.643
Where did he get it?

41:30.240 --> 41:33.403
He said he found it in your house...

41:34.600 --> 41:37.001
...that it belongs to your mother.

41:38.960 --> 41:41.964
Walter thought
she was hiding something.

41:42.280 --> 41:45.124
Something more...

41:46.080 --> 41:49.607
...and he wanted me to look into it,
but then he vanished.

41:50.960 --> 41:53.691
I think this list
might have cost Walter his life.

42:27.120 --> 42:29.122
[English - US - SDH]
